<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1433" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1433">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/373.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi><note n="127" xml:id="d1433fn127">Communicated to the Spanish Ambassador July 22, 1914.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-17">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 17, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department’s July 16, Referring to reports coming to Spanish
                                Ambassador concerning priests being shot and imprisoned, have been
                                brought to attention of Carranza.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>